Aedeagus (
Figs. 9, 10
). Pale brown, slightly shiny. In dorsal view basal part long, shortly rounded, then parallel laterally. In lateral view basal half of basal part rounded dorsally and apical half slightly narrowing dorsally. Apical part (apex) short, covered with short spines, in lateral view in form of long narrow triangle and in dorsal view broadly cross-shaped, respectively. AEB/AEA 3.47.
